  "comment": "FULL in-ring closure at D=24 (unit pi/12), AL decision 2026-07-11: a tile is in-ring iff every corner angle is an integer unit. Regular n-gon: interior 12-24/n units, integer iff n|24 => n in {3,4,6,8,12,24} (24-gon INCLUDED: 11 units, combines with star dents, e.g. 24-gon+3*d13 is a 2-corner fill; the octagon-blind zeta12 decision does not apply at D=24). Isotoxal star n*a: point a, dent 24-24/n-a, both integer iff n|24; proper star (reflex dent) iff 1 <= a <= 11-24/n. Gives 3*{1..3} 4*{1..5} 6*{1..7} 8*{1..8} 12*{1..9} 24*{1..10} = 42 star species + 6 regular = 48 tiles. Supersedes star24 (15 Myers-derived species; provably not closed under in-ring instantiation of the free-alpha families \u2014 see star-adversarial-review-2026-07-11). star24.json is kept untouched for reproducibility; famchars of shared species are identical to star24.",
